      "content": "I see. You mentioned \"neatness and control\" and making sure things don't \"draw undue attention.\" Just to clarify, are you saying that certain styles like braids, locs, or hijabs are inherently more \"distracting\" or \"unruly\" compared to more Western-style hair? I just want to understand if there's a standard of \"control\" that's actually just a preference for straight hair or specific Western aesthetics.",
